from of all my family members my grandma always believed in me. she always told me i had a big heart and i was special. always said whatever i chose to do, one day i’ll be a great artist. she raised me til i was 6 because my mom used to work in a whole different state so couldn’t be with me as often. we used to sit on a hammock and eat mandarines together. we used to do bus trips and hold hands and plan the things will do together once i get older. her death is the same date that me and my family moved here and i don’t talk about it as often cuz is so cathartic to me. i hope she knows i still wear the ring her mom gave as a gift everyday. i hope she knows i’ve built a community of my own in a place where everything has been unknown from what i thought it was home. i hope she knows i’ve chosen to be different, regardless of everyone in the family not supporting me, i have stayed still with my truth. i hope she’s proud i’ve done all the things we said will do, alone. i remember her as a very serene, kind hearted and giving woman. we were not rich but but her house was always rich of people, today is empty but full of memories that no one will take away from me.
